The paper deals with labeling algorithms for geometric objects, which is a common topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of dynamic programming algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves optimization problems, which could place it in the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of vertical line segments to connect feature points to the backbone suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper deals with minimizing the number of crossings, which could place it in the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
